@Node "--overview--" "xpkarchive.library/--overview--"


@{b}   What's new in version 2.0:@{ub}

      Version 2.0 of the xpkarchive.library brings some important new
      features to you. These include:

         - support for sublibraries for archives like lha, zoo, tar, ...
         - support for directories in archives

      Now the xpkarchive.library supports sublibraries for the handling of
      other archivetypes like those generated by e.g. zoo, lha or others.
      This allows the xpkarchive.library to handle all known and even not
      yet known kinds of archives, if you just have a sublibrary for this
      type of archive. (From now on called XAR-sublibraries and
      custom-archive)


@{b}   Archive-creation:@{ub}

      The type of archive that should be created by the xpkarchive.library
      is selected via the compression-method. If this method references an
      XPK compression-method, then it will create an XPK-archive, if it
      references a XAR compression-method, then it will call the XAR-sublib
      and this sublib creates the archive. Therefore the sublib has full
      control over the format of the archive, that should be created.
      If there are both, a XPK-method and a XAR-method, then the XAR-method
      is preferred over the XPK-method. Therefore you could have an
      xpkLHAX.library, that yould be used by the xpkmaster.library for the
      compression of single files, and a xarLHA.library, that handles the
      archive-format and compression for lha-archives.


@{b}   Adding files to archives:@{ub}

      Since XAR-sublibs create completely different archive-formats, there
      are some limitations in choosing the compression-method, when adding
      files to existing archives:

         - you cannot add files using XPK-compression to other archive-types
           than XPK-archives.

         - you cannot add files using XAR-methods to XPK-archives or to
           different custom archive-types.

      If you add a file to a custom-archive, you need not select a
      compression method any more, since it is already determined by
      the XAR-sublib.


@{b}   Extracting files from archives:@{ub}

      The xpkarchive.library determines the type of archive and chooses the
      right method for decompression. However this requires, that you have
      got the needed XPK or XAR-sublibs, that actually perform the
      decompression. Therefore you need not worry any more about the
      type of the archive to be decompressed.


@{b}   Handling of empty directories:@{ub}

      Now it is possible to add empty directories to archives; at least
      it is possible with XPK-archives. There may be some custom-archives,
      that do not support empty directories; that's not the fault of
      the xpkarchive.library but the fault of the custom archive-format.
      The name of an empty directory must end in '/', whereas filenames
      must not end in '/'. Empty directories allow you to add information
      to the archive, that affect only the directory and that is not stored
      with the normal files, e.g. a filenote of a directory. Since
      directories do not contain any other information you cannot decompress
      directories to any output media but the filesystem because it really
      would not be useful to decompress a directory e.g. to memory.


@{b}   Important changes !@{ub}

      The version-numbering has changed !
      In former versions a lower versionnumber indicated a newer file, now
      new files get a higher versionnumber. This was introduced, since the
      old method required a renumbering of the versions of a file, since the
      newest file always got the versionnumber 0 and this is not required
      with the new method any more.

      For archives that support versions, the versionnumbers are within the
      range from 1 to 65535. The versionnumber 0 has a special meaning, as
      it always references the newest file of a given filename in the
      archive. Therefore generationnumber 0 references the newest generation
      in both, the new and the old numbering-scheme. (The old
      xpkarchive.library supported only generationnumbers up to 255)

      For archives that do not support generations, a new file always gets
      the generationnumber 0 and all files with the same filename in the
      archive get deleted. (Although you should not rely on that fact !)

      It is not possible any more to delete a file by setting its
      generationnumber to 255, instead there is now a function for that
      purpose (XarDeleteFile).

      If you read archives, that were created by the old xpkarchive.library
      the generationnumbers get converted to the new style of versionnumbers.

      However, if you access archives with the old xpkarchive.library that
      were created by the new xpkarchive.library, the versionnumbers may be
      incorrect (but that should not prevent you from decompressing these
      archives with the old library, however it might fail on decompressing
      directories, since the old library did not support directories).


@EndNode

@Node "XarAddFileA()" "xpkarchive.library/XarAddFileA"

@{b}    NAME@{ub}
        XarAddFile

@{b}    SYNOPSIS@{ub}
        arclock = XarAddFileA( tags )
        D0                      A0

        XarLock * XarAddFileA( struct @{"TagItem" Link "TEXT_INCLUDE:utility/tagitem.h/Main" 31} * )


        arclock = XarAddFile( firsttag, ...)

        XarLock * XarAddFile( Tag, ...)



@{b}    FUNCTION@{ub}


        XarAddFileA() adds a file or directory to the archive. A trailing
        '/' indicates directories, filenames must not end in '/'.
        If the input-type is XAR_InName, a trailing '/' is not needed.
        Depending on the selected compression method (XAR_Method) it uses
        XPK-libraries for compression or XAR-libraries which can handle
        other archive-formats like e.g. those generated by lha or zoo.


        See also the chapter about generations.

@{b}    NOTES:@{ub}
        - a4 is preserved, therefore hooks called by this function need not
          use __saveds. See xpk/--progress-- for further information.

        - XAR_InHook may be not supported by custom-archives, because I never
          found any information on how to used them.

        - There may be some archive-types, that do not support all
          file-attributes

        - You need not specify a compression-method for custom-archives,
          since you cannot freely choose the compression-method for them.
          You can find out this compression method via @{"XarGetType()" Link "XarGetType()"}.
          If you want to add a file to a custom-archive and you specify
          a different compression method than that used for this archive,
          you will get the errorcode XARERR_WRONG_METHOD.

        - @{"Custom" Link "TEXT_INCLUDE:hardware/custom.h/Main" 26} archives may not support versionnumbers for files and/or
          several files with the same filename.

        - The version-numbering scheme has changed from version 1.3 to 2.0,
          therefore the tag XAR_AutoNextGen is obsolete now.



@{b}    TAGS@{ub}
        supported tags:
            XAR_Archive

          input specifiers:
            XAR_InName
            XAR_InFH
            XAR_InBuf
            XAR_InHook

            XAR_InLen       (The number of bytes to pack)

            XAR_FileName    (Filename in the archive)
            XAR_FileNote

            XAR_AutoNextGen (obsolete !)
            XAR_DateStamp
            XAR_Error
            XAR_Generation
            XAR_TimeDay
            XAR_TimeMonth
            XAR_TimeYear
            XAR_TimeHour
            XAR_TimeMin
            XAR_TimeSec
            XAR_CurrentTime
            XAR_CRC
            XAR_Protection

            XAR_ProgressHook

            XAR_PackMethod
            XAR_PackMode

            XAR_Password

            XPK_GetError (for XPK-archives only)

@{b}    INPUT@{ub}
        tags    - Pointer to an array of struct @{"TagItem" Link "TEXT_INCLUDE:utility/tagitem.h/Main" 31}. See xpkarchive/tags

@{b}    RESULT@{ub}
        arclock - the ArcLock of the added file or NULL, if there was an
                  error

@{b}    SEE ALSO@{ub}
        XarOpenArchive(),@{"XarExtractFileA()" Link "XarExtractFileA()"},XarNextGeneration(),XarType()
        xpkarchive/tags

@EndNode

@Node "XarCloseArchive()" "xpkarchive.library/XarCloseArchive"

@{b}    NAME@{ub}
        XarCloseArchive

@{b}    SYNOPSIS@{ub}
        err = XarCloseArchive( arc )
        D0                  A0

        LONG  XarCloseArchive(XarHandle *)

@{b}    FUNCTION@{ub}
        Closes Archive that was opened with @{"XarOpenArchiveA()" Link "XarOpenArchiveA()"}.

@{b}    INPUT@{ub}
        arc     - The ArcHandle obtained from @{"XarOpenArchiveA()" Link "XarOpenArchiveA()"}

@{b}    RESULT@{ub}
        err     - Xar error code

@{b}    SEE ALSO@{ub}
        @{"XarOpenArchiveA()" Link "XarOpenArchiveA()"}

@EndNode

@Node "XarCopyFileA()" "xpkarchive.library/XarCopyFileA"

@{b}    NAME@{ub}
        XarCopyFileA
@{b}    SYNOPSIS@{ub}
        arclock=XarCopyFileA( tags )
        D0                     A0

        XarLock *XarCopyFileA(struct @{"TagItem" Link "TEXT_INCLUDE:utility/tagitem.h/Main" 31} *)


        arclock=XarCopyFile( firsttag, ... )

        XarLock *XarCopyFile( @{"TagItem" Link "TEXT_INCLUDE:utility/tagitem.h/Main" 31}, ... )

@{b}    FUNCTION@{ub}
        With XarCopyFileA() you can copy files between two archives without
        decompressing and newly compressing them. For this the two archives
        must be of the same type. You can determine the type of an archive
        using @{"XarGetType()" Link "XarGetType()"}. The type of standard Xpk-archives is
        "XPKArchive".

@{b}    TAGS@{ub}
        supported tags:
            XAR_Error

            XAR_DestArchive
            XAR_AutoNextGen (obsolete !)
            XAR_NewName
            XAR_FileNote   (new filenote)
            XAR_NewGeneration

            XAR_ArcLock
            XAR_Archive
            XAR_FileIndex
            XAR_FileName
            XAR_Generation

@{b}    INPUT@{ub}
        tags    - Pointer to an array of struct @{"TagItem" Link "TEXT_INCLUDE:utility/tagitem.h/Main" 31}. See xpkarchive/tags

@{b}    RESULT@{ub}
        arclock - The arclock of the file in the destination archive or
                  NULL if an error happened.

@{b}    NOTE@{ub}
        @{"Custom" Link "TEXT_INCLUDE:hardware/custom.h/Main" 26} archives may not support versionnumbers for files and/or
        several files with the same filename.

        XAR_AutoNextGen is not supported any more (see chapter about
        generations).


@{b}    SEE ALSO@{ub}
        @{"XarOpenArchiveA()" Link "XarOpenArchiveA()"},XarNextGeneration(),xpkarchive/tags

@EndNode

@Node "XarDeleteFile()" "xpkarchive.library/XarDeleteFile"

@{b}    NAME@{ub}
        XarDeleteFile()

@{b}    SYNOPSIS@{ub}
        err = XarDeleteFile( xarlock )
        D0                    A0

        LONG XarDeleteFile( XarLock *)

@{b}    FUNCTION@{ub}

        Delete a file in the archive. The file may still be in the archive
        and be marked as deleted. However you may not rely on the fact, that
        it is still there and therefore the arclock may be invalid after a
        call to this function. You can check this flag via the
        macro XarIsDeleted()


@{b}    INPUT@{ub}
        xarlock - xarlock obtained by @{"XarGetLock()" Link "XarGetLock()"},@{"XarNextLock()" Link "XarNextLock()"},
                  @{"XarPrevLock()" Link "XarPrevLock()"} or @{"XarFindFileA()" Link "XarFindFileA()"}

@{b}    RESULT@{ub}
        err - Error code


@{b}    SEE ALSO@{ub}
        @{"XarGetLock()" Link "XarGetLock()"},@{"XarNextLock()" Link "XarNextLock()"},@{"XarPrevLock()" Link "XarPrevLock()"},@{"XarFindFileA()" Link "XarFindFileA()"},
        XarIsDeleted()

@EndNode

@Node "XarDirect()" "xpkarchive.library/XarDirect"

@{b}    NAME@{ub}
        XarDirect()

@{b}    SYNOPSIS@{ub}
        err = XarDirect(handle,command)
        D0                A0      A1

        LONG XarDirect(XarHandle *,UBYTE *)

@{b}    FUNCTION@{ub}

        Send a commandstring direct to the sublibrary, that handles the
        archive. This is thought for special cases, that cannot be handled
        by the other functions. E.g. the commands, that are used for the
        generationhandling of ZOO-archives are one of these cases.


@{b}    INPUT@{ub}
        handle  - Handle of the archive
        command - Commandstring


@{b}    RESULT@{ub}
        err - Error code


@{b}    NOTE@{ub}
        The error code needs not really indicate an error, but for this
        function it is also used to indicate, that there is a result-text
        from the function. Errorcodes>=XARERR_CUSTOM_LEVEL are custom error
        codes of the sublibraries and the same error-code may result in
        a different result-message every time.


@{b}    SEE ALSO@{ub}


@EndNode

@Node "XarExamine()" "xpkarchive.library/XarExamine"

@{b}    NAME@{ub}
        XarExamine()


@{b}    SYNOPSIS@{ub}
        err = XarExamine( xarlock , xfib )
        D0                  A0       A1

        LONG XarExamine( XarLock *, struct XpkFib * )


@{b}    FUNCTION@{ub}
        XarExamine() is the xpkarchive.library version of XpkExamine().
        With this function it is possible to get additional informations
        about files in the archive.
        For non-XPK archives, there is only a limited support of this
        function. For these the ID-fiels in struct XpkFib contains the
        value XAR_NULL_XPK_ID.
        Directories have everything set to 0 except CLen, which
        is set to -1.


@{b}    INPUT@{ub}
        xarlock - xarlock obtained by @{"XarGetLock()" Link "XarGetLock()"},@{"XarNextLock()" Link "XarNextLock()"},
                  @{"XarPrevLock()" Link "XarPrevLock()"} or @{"XarFindFileA()" Link "XarFindFileA()"}
        xfib    - pointer to an xpk-fib structure


@{b}    RESULT@{ub}
        err - Error code, XAR-sublibs may return
              XARERR_FUNCTION_NOT_SUPPORTED


@{b}    SEE ALSO@{ub}
        @{"XarGetLock()" Link "XarGetLock()"},@{"XarNextLock()" Link "XarNextLock()"},@{"XarPrevLock()" Link "XarPrevLock()"},@{"XarFindFileA()" Link "XarFindFileA()"}

@EndNode

@Node "XarExtractFileA()" "xpkarchive.library/XarExtractFileA"

@{b}    NAME@{ub}
        XarExtractFileA


@{b}    SYNOPSIS@{ub}
        err = XarExtractFileA( tags )
        D0                      A0

        LONG XarExtractFileA(struct @{"TagItem" Link "TEXT_INCLUDE:utility/tagitem.h/Main" 31} *)


        err = XarExtractFile( firsttag, ... )

        LONG XarExtractFile( Tag, ... )


@{b}    FUNCTION@{ub}
        This function is used to extract files from an archive and
        decompress them.
        If you select XAR_OutName and the path to the filename does not
        exist, then the xpkarchive.library will create all directories
        that are required to extract the file with the full path.
        You must not supply XPK_In - tags.


@{b}    NOTE: a4 is preserved, therefore hooks called by this function need not@{ub}
        use __saveds. See xpk/--progress-- for further information.


@{b}    TAGS@{ub}
        supported tags:

            XAR_Error
            XAR_ArcLock
            XAR_Archive
            XAR_FileIndex
            XAR_FileName
            XAR_Generation

          output specifiers:
            XAR_OutName
            XAR_OutFH
            XAR_OutBuf
            XAR_OutHook

            XAR_OutBufLen   ( Bytes to be unpacked )

            XAR_ProgressHook
            XAR_GetOutBuf
            XAR_GetOutBufLen
            XAR_GetOutLen
            XAR_OutMemType
            XAR_Password

            XPK_GetError (for XPK-archives only)


@{b}    INPUT@{ub}
        tags    - Pointer to an array of struct @{"TagItem" Link "TEXT_INCLUDE:utility/tagitem.h/Main" 31}. See xpkarchive/tags


@{b}    RESULT@{ub}
        err - Error code


@{b}    SEE ALSO@{ub}
        XarAddFile(),xpkarchive/tags

@EndNode

@Node "XarFindFileA()" "xpkarchive.library/XarFindFileA"

@{b}    NAME@{ub}
        XarFindFileA

@{b}    SYNOPSIS@{ub}
        arclock = XarFindFileA( tags )
        D0                       A0

        XarLock *XarFindFileA(struct @{"TagItem" Link "TEXT_INCLUDE:utility/tagitem.h/Main" 31} *)


        arclock = XarFindFile( firsttag, ... )

        XarLock *XarFindFile( Tag, ... )

@{b}    FUNCTION@{ub}
        Find the arclock to a given filename and generation number or
        fileindex number. Directory entries are skipped unless you
        opened the archive with XAR_ShowDirs=TRUE

@{b}    TAGS@{ub}
        supported tags:
            XAR_ArcLock
            XAR_Archive
            XAR_FileIndex
            XAR_FileName
            XAR_Generation
            XAR_Error

@{b}    INPUT@{ub}
        tags    - Pointer to an array of struct @{"TagItem" Link "TEXT_INCLUDE:utility/tagitem.h/Main" 31}. See xpkarchive/tags

@{b}    RESULT@{ub}
        arclock - the arclock of the file or NULL

@{b}    SEE ALSO@{ub}
        @{"XarNextLock()" Link "XarNextLock()"},@{"XarPrevLock()" Link "XarPrevLock()"},xpkarchive/tags

@EndNode

@Node "XarGetFileData()" "xpkarchive.library/XarGetFileData"

@{b}    NAME@{ub}
        XarGetFileData

@{b}    SYNOPSIS@{ub}
        fdata = XarGetFileData( arclock )
        D0                        A0

        struct XarExtFileData *XarGetFileData(XarLock *)

@{b}    FUNCTION@{ub}

        With this function you can get information about the file stored in
        the archive.

        NOTE: From version 2.0 on this function returns a pointer to
              an extended structure.


@{b}    INPUT@{ub}
        arclock - the arclock of an file in the archive. You can find the
                  arclock of an file using @{"XarFindFileA()" Link "XarFindFileA()"} or XarGetLock()/
                  @{"XarNextLock()/XarPrevLock()" Link "XarPrevLock()"}

@{b}    RESULT@{ub}
        fdata   - a pointer to struct XarExtFileData:

       struct XarExtFileData {
          UBYTE CHKSum;         /* FileData-Checksum (for internal use only)*/
          UBYTE Method,Version; /* Method=1 , Version=XpkBase->lib_Version  */
          UBYTE Generation;     /* Generation of the file                   */
          USHORT SysID;         /* SystemID : SYS_AMIGA                     */
          ULONG Filesize;       /* original Filesize                        */
          struct XarTime Time;  /* Date of the file                         */
          USHORT CRC;           /* Checksum of the file (optional)          */
          ULONG Protection;     /* Protectionbits                           */

         /* the following entries do not exist before version 2.0 !!!! */

          ULONG ValidMask;      /* Every set bit defines a valid Entry      */
                                /* XAR_Valid...                             */
          ULONG CompressedSize; /* Size of the compressed data              */
          ULONG CRC32;          /* CRC32 value (optional)                   */

          UBYTE Type;           /* XAR_TypeFile | XAR_TypeDir               */
          UBYTE Pad;            /* Padding                                  */

       };


@{b}    NOTE: ValidMask has bits set if the following fields have a valid@{ub}
          entry:

          Field      Symbol             Bitmask

          SysID      XAR_ValidSysID     1
          Time       XAR_ValidTime      2
          CRC        XAR_ValidCRC       4
          Protection XAR_ValidProtect   8
          CRC32      XAR_ValidCRC32    16

          These fields depend on the type of the archive.

          The other fields should have always valid entries.



@{b}    SEE ALSO@{ub}
        @{"XarFindFileA()" Link "XarFindFileA()"},@{"XarGetLock()" Link "XarGetLock()"},@{"XarNextLock()" Link "XarNextLock()"},@{"XarPrevLock()" Link "XarPrevLock()"},xpkarchive.h,
        @{"XarGetFileSize()" Link "XarGetFileSize()"}

@EndNode

@Node "XarGetFileIndex()" "xpkarchive.library/XarGetFileIndex"

@{b}    NAME@{ub}
        XarGetFileIndex

@{b}    SYNOPSIS@{ub}
        index = XarGetFileIndex( arclock )
         D0                        A0

        ULONG XarGetFileIndex(XarLock *)

@{b}    FUNCTION@{ub}
        Evaluates the position of the file in the archive.

@{b}    INPUT@{ub}
        arclock - the arclock of an file in the archive. You can find the
                  arclock of an file using @{"XarFindFileA()" Link "XarFindFileA()"} or XarGetLock()/
                  @{"XarNextLock()/XarPrevLock()" Link "XarPrevLock()"}

@{b}    RESULT@{ub}
        index   - the index of the file in the archive

@{b}    SEE ALSO@{ub}
        @{"XarFindFileA()" Link "XarFindFileA()"},@{"XarGetLock()" Link "XarGetLock()"},@{"XarNextLock()" Link "XarNextLock()"},@{"XarPrevLock()" Link "XarPrevLock()"}

@EndNode

@Node "XarGetFileName()" "xpkarchive.library/XarGetFileName"

@{b}    NAME@{ub}
        XarGetFileName

@{b}    SYNOPSIS@{ub}
        filename = XarGetFileName( arclock )
           D0                        A0

        UBYTE *XarGetFileName(XarLock *)

@{b}    FUNCTION@{ub}
        Determines the filename of the file, that is identified by arclock.

@{b}    INPUT@{ub}
        arclock - the arclock of an file in the archive. You can find the
                  arclock of an file using XarGetLock()/XarNextLock()/
                  @{"XarPrevLock()" Link "XarPrevLock()"}

@{b}    RESULT@{ub}
        filename - the filename
@{b}    SEE ALSO@{ub}
        @{"XarGetLock()" Link "XarGetLock()"},@{"XarNextLock()" Link "XarNextLock()"},@{"XarPrevLock()" Link "XarPrevLock()"}

@EndNode

@Node "XarGetFileNote()" "xpkarchive.library/XarGetFileNote"

@{b}    NAME@{ub}
        XarGetFileNote

@{b}    SYNOPSIS@{ub}
        filenote = XarGetFileNote( arclock )
           D0                        A0

        UBYTE *XarGetFileNote(XarLock *)

@{b}    FUNCTION@{ub}
        Determines the filename of the file, that is identified by arclock.

@{b}    INPUT@{ub}
        arclock - the arclock of an file in the archive. You can find the
                  arclock of an file using XarGetLock()/XarNextLock()/
                  @{"XarPrevLock()" Link "XarPrevLock()"}

@{b}    RESULT@{ub}
        filenote - the filenote of the file or NULL, if there is
                   no filenote.


@{b}    SEE ALSO@{ub}
        @{"XarGetLock()" Link "XarGetLock()"},@{"XarNextLock()" Link "XarNextLock()"},@{"XarPrevLock()" Link "XarPrevLock()"}

@EndNode

@Node "XarGetFileSize()" "xpkarchive.library/XarGetFileSize"

@{b}    NAME@{ub}
        XarGetFileSize
@{b}    SYNOPSIS@{ub}
        filesize = XarGetFileSize( arclock )
           D0                        A0

        ULONG XarGetFileSize(XarLock *)

@{b}    FUNCTION@{ub}
        Determines the compressed size of the file, that is identified by
        arclock.

@{b}    INPUT@{ub}
        arclock - the arclock of an file in the archive. You can find the
                  arclock of an file using XarGetLock()/XarNextLock()/
                  @{"XarPrevLock()" Link "XarPrevLock()"}

@{b}    RESULT@{ub}
        filesize - the compressed size of the file

@{b}    NOTE: since version 2.0 you can also determine the compressed size@{ub}
          via XarGetFileData.


@{b}    SEE ALSO@{ub}
        @{"XarGetLock()" Link "XarGetLock()"},@{"XarNextLock()" Link "XarNextLock()"},@{"XarPrevLock()" Link "XarPrevLock()"}

@EndNode

@Node "XarGetLock()" "xpkarchive.library/XarGetLock"

@{b}    NAME@{ub}
        XarGetLock
@{b}    SYNOPSIS@{ub}
        arclock = XarGetLock( arc )
          D0                  A0


        XarLock * XarGetLock( XarHandle *)

@{b}    FUNCTION@{ub}
        This function gets the first entry of the contents list of the
        archive. The arclock returned by this function can be used to get
        further information of the file or to get the next or previous
        entry in the file using @{"XarNextLock()" Link "XarNextLock()"} or @{"XarPrevLock()" Link "XarPrevLock()"}.

        Directories are hidden away, if you do not set XAR_ShowDirs when
        opening the archive.

@{b}    INPUT@{ub}
        arc - The archandle returned by @{"XarOpenArchiveA()" Link "XarOpenArchiveA()"}

@{b}    RESULT@{ub}
        arclock - the identifier of a file in the archive, or NULL if the
        archive is empty.

@{b}    SEE ALSO@{ub}
        @{"XarNextLock()" Link "XarNextLock()"}, @{"XarPrevLock()" Link "XarPrevLock()"} ,@{"XarOpenArchiveA()" Link "XarOpenArchiveA()"}

@EndNode

@Node "XarGetPackMode()" "xpkarchive.library/XarGetPackMode"

@{b}    NAME@{ub}
        XarGetPackMode
@{b}    SYNOPSIS@{ub}
        error = XarGetPackMode( lock, modeinfo )
          D0                     A0      A1


        LONG XarGetPackMode( XarLock *, struct XarPackMode *)

@{b}    FUNCTION@{ub}

        Get information about the compression method, that was used to pack
        a file. "modeinfo" contains the following informations, if
        XarGetPackMode() succeeds:


        UBYTE ID[9];      /* ID of the packer                              */

        UBYTE Description[10];
                          /* Description of the compression mode           */

        SHORT Mode;       /* Mode to select the packmode, the file was     */
                          /* with. Or -1, if unknown (or for directories)  */
                          /* Note, that this may be different from the     */
                          /* one, that was given for packing, it is just   */
                          /* within the same range of packmodes            */
                          /* e.g. if the packmethod has two modes with the */
                          /* ranges 0..49 and 50..100 and you packed the   */
                          /* file with mode 69, then 'Mode' may have any   */
                          /* value within 50..100                          */

@{b}    INPUT@{ub}
        lock - XarLock of the file

@{b}    RESULT@{ub}
        error code

@{b}    SEE ALSO@{ub}

@EndNode

@Node "XarGetType()" "xpkarchive.library/XarGetType"

@{b}    NAME@{ub}
        XarGetType

@{b}    SYNOPSIS@{ub}
        type = XarGetType( arc )
         D0                A0

        struct XarType * XarGetType( XarHandle * )

@{b}    FUNCTION@{ub}

        XarType returns a pointer to the following structure:

        struct XarType {
           UBYTE  ArchiveType[24];   /* Archive-type e.g.: lha, zoo, ...   */

         /* The following fields are not valid before version 2.0 */

           UBYTE  DefaultID[9];      /* ID the packer goes by (XAR format) */
           UWORD  DefaultMode;       /* default packmode                   */
        };


        ArchiveType contains the type of the archive. Archives created with
        the xpkarchive.library and XPK-compression-methods have the type
        "XPKArchive". For these is: DefaultID="", DefaultMode=0

        For custom-archives, ArchiveType contains the archive-type,
        DefaultID the ID of the XAR-library that was used to build this
        archive and DefaultMode the default compression-mode used by this
        XAR-library.

@{b}    INPUT@{ub}
        arc - The archandle returned by @{"XarOpenArchiveA()" Link "XarOpenArchiveA()"}

@{b}    RESULT@{ub}
        type - The type of the archive as a null-terminated string.

@{b}    SEE ALSO@{ub}
        @{"XarOpenArchiveA()" Link "XarOpenArchiveA()"}

@EndNode

@Node "XarIsDeleted()" "xpkarchive.library/XarIsDeleted"

@{b}    NAME@{ub}
