@Node "XarModifyFileDataA()" "xpkarchive.library/XarModifyFileDataA"

@{b}    NAME@{ub}
        XarModifyFileDataA()

@{b}    SYNOPSIS@{ub}
        err = XarModifyFileDataA( tags )
        D0                         A0

        LONG XarModifyFileDataA(struct @{"TagItem" Link "TEXT_INCLUDE:utility/tagitem.h/Main" 31} *)


        err = XarModifyFileData( firsttag, ... )

        LONG XarModifyFileData( Tag, ... )

@{b}    FUNCTION@{ub}
        This function is used to modify entries in the XarExtFileData
        structure, that is bound to every file.

        NOTE: it is not possible to change some fields in the XarExtFileData
              structure:

                    FileSize,CHKSum,CompressedSize

              Some archive-types may not support some of these fields !


@{b}    TAGS@{ub}
        supported tags:
            XAR_Error
            XAR_ArcLock
            XAR_Archive
            XAR_FileIndex
            XAR_FileName
            XAR_Generation
            XAR_TimeDay
            XAR_TimeMonth
            XAR_TimeYear
            XAR_TimeHour
            XAR_TimeMin
            XAR_TimeSec
            XAR_DateStamp
            XAR_CRC
            XAR_CRC32 (V2)
            XAR_ValidMask   (actually I think it is not a good idea to modify
                             this entry, but maybe it might be useful)
            XAR_Protection
            XAR_NewGeneration

@{b}    INPUT@{ub}
        tags    - Pointer to an array of struct @{"TagItem" Link "TEXT_INCLUDE:utility/tagitem.h/Main" 31}. See xpkarchive/tags

@{b}    RESULT@{ub}
        err - Error code

@{b}    NOTE@{ub}

        You cannot delete files with this function any more as it was
        possible in earlier versions by setting the generationnumber to
        XAR_FileDeleted ! Use @{"XarDeleteFile()" Link "XarDeleteFile()"} instead.



@{b}    SEE ALSO@{ub}
        @{"XarGetFileData()" Link "XarGetFileData()"},@{"XarDeleteFile()" Link "XarDeleteFile()"},@{"XarUndeleteFile()" Link "XarUndeleteFile()"},xpkarchive/tags

@EndNode

