@Node "XarNextLock()" "xpkarchive.library/XarNextLock"

@{b}    NAME@{ub}
        XarNextLock()

@{b}    SYNOPSIS@{ub}
        arclock = XarNextLock( arclock )
          D0                      A0

        XarLock * XarNextLock ( XarLock * )

@{b}    FUNCTION@{ub}
        Get the next entry of the contents list.

        Directories are hidden away, if you do not set XAR_ShowDirs when
        opening the archive.


@{b}    INPUT@{ub}
        arclock - The arclock of a file

@{b}    RESULT@{ub}
        arclock - The arclock of the next file in the archive or NULL, if
                  there is no file left.

@{b}    SEE ALSO@{ub}
        @{"XarPrevLock()" Link "XarPrevLock()"}, @{"XarGetLock()" Link "XarGetLock()"}

@EndNode

@Node "XarOpenArchiveA()" "xpkarchive.library/XarOpenArchiveA"

@{b}    NAME@{ub}
        XarOpenArchiveA

@{b}    SYNOPSIS@{ub}
        arc = XarOpenArchiveA( tags )
        D0                  A0

        XarHandle *XarOpenArchiveA(struct @{"TagItem" Link "TEXT_INCLUDE:utility/tagitem.h/Main" 31} *)


        arc = XarOpenArchive( firsttag, ... )

        XarHandle *XarOpenArchive( Tag, ... )

@{b}    FUNCTION@{ub}
        Opens an archive from disk and scans through the archive for
        building the table of contents of the archive. You can access this
        list using @{"XarGetLock()" Link "XarGetLock()"} to get the first entry and XarNextLock()/
        @{"XarPrevLock()" Link "XarPrevLock()"} to get the next/previous entry.

        Since version 2.0 the xpkarchive.library is able to support other
        archive-types using XAR-sublibs. XarOpenArchiveA() automatically
        detects the archive-type.


@{b}    INPUT@{ub}
        tags    - XAR_ArchiveName: The filename of the archive

                  XAR_ArchiveMode:
                     There are three modes to open an archive:
                        XAR_ModeOldArchive:
                              Only existing archives will be opened. If it
                              does not exist XarOpenArchiveA will fail. This
                              is the default mode.
                        XAR_ModeNewArchive:
                              Existing files will be deleted and a new, empty
                              archive will be created.
                        XAR_ModeAppend:
                              Creates an archive if none exists and opens the
                              archive if one exists.


                  XAR_ShowDirs (BOOL) (V2)
                     Set this to TRUE, if you want to see directory entries.
                     If set to FALSE (default) directory-entries, which
                     describe empty directories are hidden away for
                     compatibility reasons with version 1.0 of the
                     xpkarchive.library.


                - See also xpkarchive/tags

@{b}    RESULT@{ub}
      XarHandle * if successful NULL else

@{b}    SEE ALSO@{ub}
      @{"XarCloseArchive()" Link "XarCloseArchive()"},@{"XarGetLock()" Link "XarGetLock()"}

@EndNode

@Node "XarPackArchive()" "xpkarchive.library/XarPackArchive"

@{b}    NAME@{ub}
        XarPackArchive

@{b}    SYNOPSIS@{ub}
        err = XarPackArchive( from, to )
        D0                     A0   A1

        LONG XarPackArchiveA( XarHandle *, XarHandle *)

@{b}    FUNCTION@{ub}

        Packs the contents from one archive to another (empty) archive.
        Only files, that are not deleted are copied to the other archive.
        This is also the main use for this function: it removes deleted
        files and other information from the archive, that is not needed
        any more (e.g. old filenames or old filenotes, which are just
        superseeded, when you rename files or set a new filenote).

@{b}    INPUT@{ub}
        from  - XarHandle of the archive, which should be packed.
        to    - XarHandle of the archive, to which the files are packed to.

@{b}    RESULT@{ub}

        Error-Code

@EndNode

@Node "XarPrevLock()" "xpkarchive.library/XarPrevLock"

@{b}    NAME@{ub}
        XarPrevLock()

@{b}    SYNOPSIS@{ub}
        arclock = XarPrevLock( arclock )
          D0                      A0

        XarLock * XarPrevLock ( XarLock * )

@{b}    FUNCTION@{ub}
        Get the previous entry of the contents list.

        Directories are hidden away, if you do not set XAR_ShowDirs when
        opening the archive.


@{b}    INPUT@{ub}
        arclock - The arclock of a file

@{b}    RESULT@{ub}
        arclock - The arclock of the previous file in the archive or NULL,
                  if there is no file left.

@{b}    SEE ALSO@{ub}
        @{"XarNextLock()" Link "XarNextLock()"}, @{"XarGetLock()" Link "XarGetLock()"}

@EndNode

@Node "XarProgress()" "xpkarchive.library/XarProgress"

@{b}    NAME@{ub}
        XarProgress()

@{b}    SYNOPSIS@{ub}
        result = XarProgress( type, xio, xprog, upos, cpos )
          D0                   D0   A0    A1     D1    D2

        LONG XarProgress( LONG, struct XarSubIO *, struct XarProgress *,
                          LONG, LONG)

@{b}    FUNCTION@{ub}

        This function is for XAR-sublibs only !

        It provides a simple to use interface for the calling of the
        progress-hookfunction by a sublibrary. Especially it calculates
        the required compression/decompression-speed for you.

        The first call to this function must be XARPROG_START.
        Subsequent calls must have XARPROG_MID except for the last one
        which must be XARPROG_END. XarProgress uses these types to
        determine if it needs to initialize some fields in the XarProgress-
        structure and to determine which texts need to be printed.

        At least you must call this function twice for every file,
        once with type XARPROG_START and once with type XARPROG_END.

        The XarProgress-structure needs to be initialized as follows:

        struct XarProgress {
           UBYTE *PackerName; /* Brief name of the packer                */
           UBYTE *LongName;   /* Descriptive name of packer being used   */
           UBYTE *ActActive;  /* Packing/unpacking message               */
                              /* e.g. "compressing"                      */
           UBYTE *ActDone;    /* Packing/unpacking message when done     */
                              /* e.g. "compressed"                       */

       /* The following fields are private, they need not be initialized */

           ULONG State;
           ULONG Freq;
           ULONG StartTime;
           ULONG Time;
        };


@{b}    INPUT@{ub}

        type  - XARPROG_START | XARPROG_MID | XARPROG_END | XARPROG_DIRECTORY
        xio   - the XarSubIO structure you got from the xpkarchive.library
        xprog - an initialized XarProgress structure
        upos  - the number of uncompressed bytes so far
        cpos  - the number of compressed bytes so far


@{b}    NOTE@{ub}

        In XarsAddFile you should use XARPROG_START, XARPROG_MID and
        XARPROG_END whereas in XarsAddDir you should use only
        XARPROG_DIRECTORY and then you should initialize ActActive
        with NULL.

        For directories you should call this function just once.


@{b}    RESULT@{ub}

        TRUE if the user wants to abort the compression/decompression


@{b}    SEE ALSO@{ub}
        The chapter for the progress-interface

@EndNode

@Node "XarQueryA()" "xpkarchive.library/XarQueryA"

@{b}    NAME@{ub}
        XarQueryA()

@{b}    SYNOPSIS@{ub}
        ret = XarQueryA( tags )
         D0               A0

        LONG XarQueryA ( struct @{"TagItem" Link "TEXT_INCLUDE:utility/tagitem.h/Main" 31} * )


        ret = XarQuery( firsttag, ... )

        LONG XarQuery ( Tag, ... )

@{b}    FUNCTION@{ub}

        This function is used to gain informations about the different
        archivers and compression-methods.


        You can get three different types of information depending on the
        supplied tags:


        XAR_ArchiversQuery (struct XarArchiverEntry *) :

            This returns a list of archivers and compression-methods in
            the supplied array. The length of this array must be given
            via XAR_ArraySize (LONG). The returned value gives the number
            of available packing-methods/archivers. You can find out the
            number of packers/archivers, if you supply a NULL-pointer
            for the array or an array-size less or equal to 0.


        XAR_ArchiverQuery (struct XarArchiverInfo *) :

            With this you can gain information about a specific
            packer/archiver. It fills in the values for the given
            structure. You must also supply a packmethod via
            XAR_PackMethod (UBYTE *).


        XAR_ModeQuery (struct XpkMode *) :

            It gets information about a certain compression-mode given
            by XAR_PackMode (LONG) of a packer/archiver given by
            XAR_PackMethod (UBYTE *).  If there is no mode given, then
            it will fill in information about the default-mode.


@{b}    RESULT@{ub}

        Number of packers/archivers available for XAR_ArchiversQuery

        0 for the other queries.

@EndNode

@Node "XarRenameFileA()" "xpkarchive.library/XarRenameFileA"

@{b}    NAME@{ub}
        XarRenameFileA()

@{b}    SYNOPSIS@{ub}
        err = XarRenameFileA( tags )
        D0                     A0

        LONG XarRenameFileA(struct @{"TagItem" Link "TEXT_INCLUDE:utility/tagitem.h/Main" 31} *)


        err = XarRenameFile( firsttag, ... )

        LONG XarRenameFile( Tag, ... )

@{b}    FUNCTION@{ub}
        In archives of the type "XPKArchive" it is possible to rename files.
        Some custom archives might support renaming of files, too.
        Using this function you can set a new filename and generationnumber.

@{b}    TAGS@{ub}
        supported tags:
            XAR_ArcLock
            XAR_Archive
            XAR_FileIndex
            XAR_FileName
            XAR_Generation
            XAR_Error
            XAR_NewName
            XAR_NewGeneration
            XAR_AutoNextGen    (obsolete !)

@{b}    INPUT@{ub}
        tags    - Pointer to an array of struct @{"TagItem" Link "TEXT_INCLUDE:utility/tagitem.h/Main" 31}. See xpkarchive/tags


@{b}    NOTE@{ub}
        This function may not be supported by custom-archives.

        @{"Custom" Link "TEXT_INCLUDE:hardware/custom.h/Main" 26} archives may not support versionnumbers for files and/or
        several files with the same filename.

@{b}    RESULT@{ub}
        err - Error code

@{b}    SEE ALSO@{ub}
        XarModifyFileData(), @{"XarGetType()" Link "XarGetType()"}

@EndNode

